gure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/c0fe9cb56250e9d73b375f6b4675bf78.png\" alt=\"The Auto Unlock screen with a message in the center of the screen that says the Mac is being unlocked with Apple Watch.\" height=\"290\" width=\"466\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0970_AutoUnlock.png\"></figure><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Note\"><em>Note: </em>To use Auto Unlock, your Mac (a mid-2013 or later model) must have macOS Sierra or later installed and your Apple Watch must have watchOS 3 or later installed. You must be <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">signed in to iCloud</a> using the same <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=apple-id&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH22612FA790&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Apple ID</a> on both devices, and <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=two-factor-authentication&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLCA9A0AAD&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">two-factor authentication</a> must be turned on for your Apple ID. Make sure your Apple Watch is unlocked.</p></div><div id=\"mchldd60c5b3\" class=\"Task no-header\"><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchldd60c5b3\"><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p><em>Turn on Auto Unlock on your Mac: </em>Choose Apple menu <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/e043ddf1a45711e13f0b30612db65e21.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo.png\"> &gt; System Preferences, click Security &amp; Privacy, then select the “Allow your Apple Watch to unlock your Mac” checkbox.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.preference.security\" class=\"URL\">Open Security &amp; Privacy preferences for me</a></p><p>If necessary, click the lock icon <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/314aad0915d1135d3070820482bc2166.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_LockSysPrefs_osx.png\"> at the bottom of the pane, then type an <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=administrator&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL17F139FC&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">administrator</a> name and password.</p></li><li><p><em>Unlock your Mac: </em>Wake your Mac from its idle state by pressing any keyboard key or, on a portable, by opening the display. The screen indicates your Mac is being unlocked.</p></li></ul></div></div><p>System Information can confirm if your Mac supports Auto Unlock. Choose Apple menu &gt; About This Mac, then click System Report. In the sidebar, click Network, click Wi-Fi, then look in the Interfaces section for Auto Unlock.</p><p>If you’re the administrator for another user on your Mac, you can log in to their user account and turn on Auto Unlock for them, as long as their Apple ID uses two-factor authentication and their Apple Watch has watchOS 3 installed.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up iCloud</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=continuity&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL1D734309&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use Continuity to work across Apple devices</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-the-login-password-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1550&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change the login password on Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Unarchived","name":"Unarchived","englishName":"Unarchived","displayName":"Unarchived","articleCount":"10186"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"7818"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"SupportSearchIndexOFF","name":"SupportSearchIndexOFF","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexOFF","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexOFF","articleCount":"6283"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac"